Ad Text:
We're partnering with one of Australia’s leading banks, currently seeking a Business Analyst to join a collaborative squad delivering a large-scale transformation.

$800 + super
12 month contract
Hybrid working – Sydney
This is the chance to work on a multi-year transformation program focused on driving meaningful change across core banking systems and customer products.

What you’ll be doing:

Business Analysis: Elicit, document and validate detailed business and functional requirements across complex banking initiatives.
Stakeholder Management: Engage confidently with business, technology and delivery stakeholders to align requirements, manage expectations and support successful outcomes.
Data Migration: Support data migration activities including mapping, validation, reconciliation and defect resolution across legacy and target systems.
What we’re looking for:

Proven experience as a Business Analyst within banking or financial services.
Strong stakeholder management skills with the ability to influence and build trust across varied teams.
Hands-on experience supporting data migration in large-scale programs.
Solid understanding of consumer banking products viewed favourably.
This is an exciting opportunity to contribute to a major transformation within a leading Australian bank, gaining exposure to complex systems and long-term strategic change. If of interest, please apply!

About the Department

The Department of Health, Disability and Ageing leads national policy and programs that support the health, wellbeing and independence of Australians.

Working across health, aged care and disability reform, the Department partners with governments, providers and communities to deliver accessible, person-centred services and strengthen Australia's care systems for the future.

About the Role

One labour hire contractor is being sought to review, evaluate and provide advice regarding changes to aged care provider financial reporting in the Quarterly Financial Report (QFR) and Aged Care Financial Report (ACFR) data collections.

The role will work as part of a small team to review and recommend future changes to the QFR and ACFR data collections to ensure they are collecting fit-for-purpose data for changing policy and programs whilst also trying to streamline reporting and reduce the administrative burden of financial reporting for aged care providers. The role will also be required to design a multi-dimensional chart of accounts for the QFR and ACFR to manage the flow of data through the department's IT systems.

We require a highly skilled candidate who can quickly understand the intricacies of aged care provider financial reporting and provide advice regarding changes to the financial reporting. The candidates will hold Certified Practicing Accountant (CPA) or Chartered Accountant (CA) credentials or hold an accounting/finance degree or qualification. Experience in health/aged care sector financial reporting is also highly desirable.

Key Duties

Provide specialist analysis and advice on aged care provider financial reporting matters.
Propose, analyse and assess requests for changes to the QFR and ACFR data collections and definitions, adhering to prescribed Principles and Drivers.
Develop and update templates, resources and guidance materials to support aged care providers meeting their financial reporting responsibilities.
Lead the preparation of briefing materials and presentations to support consultation with stakeholders and advice to Senior Executives as decision makers.
Lead stakeholder engagement with aged care providers, teams across the Ageing and Aged Care Group, the Independent Health and Aged Care Pricing Authority and the Aged Care Quality and Safety Commission.
Coordinating work activities including planning, scheduling, reporting and managing risks as appropriate.

Required Capabilities

Specialist technical accounting / financial reporting capability, including the ability to undertake analysis and provide advice regarding financial data and reporting matters.
Strong stakeholder management, interpersonal and communication skills, including the ability to build and maintain effective working relationships with internal and external stakeholders.
Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to provide succinct and accurate technical advice.
Ability to work independently under limited direction, respond flexibly to change, think critically, analyse and solve complex problems and make decisions using research and analysis, good judgement, expertise and knowledge.
Demonstrates strong attention to detail, ensuring accuracy and consistency in all tasks and documentation.
Demonstrated planning and organisational skills, including ability to meet deadlines with competing priorities in a complex, changing and high-pressure environment.

How to Apply

Click APPLY or contact Marisa Conlon, Senior Consultant, Talent Acquisition at marisa@fprs.com.au for further information on the role.

Please submit applications in Word format only by 10am, 11th March 2026.

Job Title: Senior Functional Business Analyst – Supply Chain

This role is a immediate start.

This role will see you working directly with enterprise clients across Australia, leading structured discovery sessions and translating operational requirements into clear, delivery-ready workflows.

Work on large-scale national supply chain transformation programs

High-impact, client-facing consulting environment

Exposure to ERP, SAP MM and complex multi-system integrations

Agile or hybrid delivery experience

Essential

12 month contract
Sydney CBD location
Salesforce CRM focus

Ignite is Australia's preferred partner in recruitment and technology solutions across private and public sectors.

We are seeking a highly skilled and motivated Data Scientist for a client in the mining and resources industry. This is on a day rate contract on an initial 6 months with potential extension/conversion to permanent. The role is based in Brisbane CBD office with hybrid working week.

The ideal candidate will have 3-5 years of relevant experience and be proficient in SQL and Python. Experience with Power BI is a bonus, and familiarity with LLM (Large Language Models) is highly advantageous. A willingness to learn and adapt to new tools and technologies is essential for this role.

Key Responsibilities:

Analyze and interpret large datasets to derive actionable insights.

Develop and implement data models using Python and SQL.

Create and optimize data pipelines for automated data processing.

Collaborate with stakeholders to understand business requirements and deliver data-driven solutions.

(Optional) Utilize Power BI for reporting and visualizations.

Required Skills & Experience:

3-5 years of experience as a Data Scientist or in a similar role.

Proficiency in SQL and Python.

Strong problem-solving and analytical skills.

Ability to work independently and as part of a team.

Willingness to learn and adapt to new technologies and methods.

Bonus Skills:

Experience with Power BI for data visualization.

Knowledge of Large Language Models (LLM).

Please note that we are only able to consider Brisbane based candidates due to in office requirements and candidates must have full working rights in Australia to be considered.

About Us

Join us at Cleanaway and contribute to making a sustainable future possible, together.

We transform waste into resources and renewable energy.  When you start to think of waste as a resource, it opens a world of possibilities.

As a high growth, ASX listed organisation with over 10,000 employees, our goal is to be recognised by our customers as the most innovative and sustainable waste management company with industry leading HSE performance.  We are Australia’s largest company in this sector, providing essential services to millions of customers and communities nationally.

The Opportunity

We are seeking a commercially astute Senior Pricing Analyst to deliver actionable insights and drive profitable growth across the business. This role blends data analysis, operational understanding and commercial acumen to partner with Finance and Sales in developing and executing value-based pricing strategies.

You will provide insights to pricing discussions using customer and market research, cost analysis, lifecycle modelling and competitor intelligence. You’ll identify revenue growth opportunities across sales, volume and customer segments, commercialise initiatives, and support decision-making through robust reporting and forecasting tools.

The role also involves developing and maintaining revenue management frameworks, playbooks and models to ensure consistency, alignment and effective change management across the organisation.

 About You

Strong analytical background with demonstrated commercial expertise
Experience delivering data-driven insights and reporting solutions
Proven ability to influence and partner with stakeholders at all levels, including executive
Experience managing multiple projects across business units and products
Strong financial and commercial acumen
Working knowledge of SQL, Tableau, Alteryx or similar analytical tools
Understanding of commercial and economic principles
Experience applying project management methodologies and documenting processes

If you are a strategic thinker who thrives on turning data into commercial impact, we’d love to hear from you.

Why join Cleanaway? 

Competitive salary package
Flexible working arrangements
Career opportunities in a high growth, Australian business
Supportive and safe work environment
Paid parental leave
Great company benefits: Employee share program, company discounts, salary packaging, flu vaccinations, EAP, discounts on private health insurance and more.

Our Process

Our recruitment process involves a number of checks including, but not limited to, criminal history, medicals, drug & alcohol testing, as well as verification of qualifications, licences and right-to-work status.

We are dedicated to improving employment outcomes and encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples. We also welcome candidates of all ages, abilities, gender identities, experiences (including veterans), and cultural backgrounds.

If you require any adjustments during the recruitment process, please contact us by emailing inclusion@cleanaway.com.au.

Join us on our exciting journey towards a sustainable future.

Simply click the Apply button or visit https://www.cleanaway.com.au/about-us/careers and let's make a positive impact together.

We are seeking a Senior Business Analyst to join a fast-paced retail technology team on a temporary basis. This is an exciting opportunity to contribute to impactful projects in Hawthorn East.

Join a team that values expertise and is dedicated to driving success in the retail industry. If you're ready to take on this exciting role as a Senior Business Analyst, we encourage you to apply today

We are looking for an experienced Integration Analyst to join our clients delivery team for a strategic project. This engagement centers on a multi-year digital transformation roadmap, specifically the modernisation of their contact center ecosystem.

The successful candidate will lead the technical transition from legacy Dynamics 365 Unified Service Desk (USD) environments to the AI-driven Microsoft Copilot Service Workspace (CSW), with a target completion of June 2028.

Key Responsibilities
Solution Design: Act as a consultative bridge, converting complex business cases into robust technical documentation and architectural blueprints.
Modernisation Lead: Navigate the transition from legacy on-premise hardware to a flexible, cloud-based CCaaS (Contact Centre as a Service) platform.
Workflow Visualisation: Use Visio or Web sequence diagrams to clearly depict and communicate integration workflows to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Azure Integration: Design and implement integration patterns and approaches leveraging Azure Artefacts and associated cloud tools.
Technical Troubleshooting: Apply proven diagnostic skills to solve deep-tier integration issues within the SDLC.
Required Knowledge & Skills
Technical Stack: Strong proficiency in Azure Integration and a solid understanding of the Microsoft Copilot Service Workspace (CSW) roadmap.
Process Mastery: Deep working knowledge of Agile development practices and the principles of the Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC).
Tooling: Proficiency with JIRA for job scheduling/sprint management, and Confluence/Wiki for project documentation.
Communication: Exceptional interpersonal and consultative skills; you must be comfortable working both as a solo lead and as part of a high-velocity team.
Analytical Skills: Excellent ability to evaluate industry trends and practices to ensure the client's architecture remains future-proof.
Professional Qualities
Strong verbal and written communication skills with a focus on negotiation and decision-making.
Ability to collaborate effectively in a team environment or operate autonomously when required.
Sound problem-solving skills with a "diagnostic first" mindset.

And all Randstad Technologies contractors receive:

Access to a Udemy license for ongoing learning and continuous professional development
Access to exclusive discounts across various platforms
Discounts on private health funds



For more information, or to apply for this role, please contact Clayton on clayton.bradfield@randstaddigital.com.au

About CTM 
CTM is a global award-winning provider of innovative and cost-effective travel management solutions to the corporate, events, leisure and loyalty travel markets. CTM provides personalised service excellence with client-facing technology solutions in offices all around the world, including New Zealand, Australia, Asia, North America and Europe with over 3000 employees.
  
At CTM, our people are our greatest asset. We are a team of collaborative, innovative and future focused professionals we work with the company's values in mind; Connect, Deliver and Evolve.

About the Role 
The purpose of the role is to provide leadership, oversight and governance to design, govern and oversee the implementation of data standards and integrity of CTM's data assets across all global and regional operations.
 
The role ensures that data used for decision-making, reporting and customer engagement is consistent and trusted. It establishes and maintains the frameworks, standards and controls that protect CTM's data assets and ensures alignment with internal assurance requirements.
 
As the global authority for data standards, this position promotes a culture of accountability and continuous improvement in data management practices. This role also integrates inputs across Account Management, Sales, Customer, Operations and Finance to ensure data standards directly enable exceptional client insights, commercial modelling, operational forecasting, supplier strategy and the monetisation and productisation of CTM's data assets. By ensuring global consistency and accuracy of data, this role underpins CTM's capability to deliver differentiated insights to customers and create enterprise-wide commercial value.
 
Responsibilities
The responsibilities of this role span enterprise governance, cross-functional alignment and the ongoing uplift of CTM's global data standards, ensuring data is trusted and able to deliver meaningful commercial, operational and client value.

Establish and Maintain Enterprise Data Frameworks - Design and oversee enterprise-wide data standards, policies, business rules and control frameworks that safeguard the accuracy and integrity of CTM's data assets across all global systems and processes, ensuring standards reflect multi-domain business inputs and operational, commercial and customer-facing requirements.
Provide Strategic Leadership and Oversight - Lead CTM's data standards and control programmes to strengthen governance maturity, drive continuous improvement, ensuring all standards support future innovation, platform convergence and enterprise-wide insight generation.
Promote Effective Communication and Engagement - Communicate data standard policies and key insights across global and regional teams to embed consistent understanding and accountability, translating complex dependencies into clear business impacts for Sales, Account Management, Customer and Operations leaders.
Report on Data Standards and Integrity - Provide regular and transparent reporting to executive leadership on data standard performance, control effectiveness and risk mitigation, highlighting commercial, client and operational impacts associated with data quality uplift.
Drive Behavioural Change - Champion a culture of data stewardship and continuous improvement by influencing behaviours, aligning practices, fostering shared ownership of data accuracy across all job families.
Enable Commercial and Client-Facing Value - Ensure data standards directly support CTM's ability to deliver premium insights to customers, enhance supplier negotiations, strengthen forecasting accuracy and develop new data-driven products and commercial propositions.
Why CTM?  
As a global organisation CTM offers a range of employee benefits that including;

Travel discounts  
Perkbox - Retail, Lifestyle, Entertainment, Health & Wellness discounts 
Training and Development opportunities  
Annual Volunteer Day  
x2 Wellness/Chillout Days  
Blended work arrangements with hybrid WFH flexibility 
2 Weeks extra leave - Purchase Leave
CTM offer a strong, established and sustainable work environment which will support your career development and wellbeing.
  
CTM is committed to the unique contributions of all our people and actively encourage candidates with all abilities and diverse backgrounds to apply. Come work for a global award winning company that values its people, community, and technological innovation.

About us

FISHBOWL is one of Australia’s most trusted brands on a mission to change the culture around fast food. Founded in 2016 in Bondi, the brand has expanded to over 50 stores across Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, the Gold Coast, and more recently, New York. With our continued growth, our focus is now on elevating and refining all aspects of the brand, instilling a culture of excellence in our head office, and supporting our team in-store to deliver the best product and experience to our customers.




About the role

At FISHBOWL, we believe great decisions are powered by great data. This is a newly created, standalone Senior Commercial Analyst role reporting directly to the Chief Financial Officer.

You will own end-to-end FP&A across the group, covering budgeting, forecasting management reporting and commercial analysis for both our Australian operations and our growing presence in the US (currently three stores).




Skills and experience

This role requires a highly capable and commercially astute finance professional who combines strong technical modelling skills with sound judgement, intellectual curiosity, and exceptional attention to detail.

You’ll have:

5+ years’ experience in FP&A, commercial finance or a related role within a fast-paced, multi-site retail, FMCG or QSR environment, with increasing levels of responsibility

Demonstrated experience owning end-to-end budgeting and rolling forecast processes, including assumption setting and stakeholder alignment

Proven experience preparing Board-ready management reporting and executive-level presentations

Strong commercial acumen with the ability to interpret financial results in an operational context and translate insights into clear business implications

Exceptional attention to detail, with a rigorous quality-control mindset and a track record of delivering highly accurate outputs

High intellectual curiosity and a willingness to investigate and challenge when results do not “look right”

Advanced financial modelling capability (including scenario and sensitivity analysis) with expert-level Excel skills; experience with BI tools (e.g. Power BI) desirable

Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to distil complex analysis into clear, actionable insights

Comfortable operating with significant autonomy in a lean environment

CA/CPA qualification advantageous

Management consulting or strategy experience desirable.




Responsibilities

The right candidate will bring a structured, hypothesis-led problem-solving approach - able to frame ambiguous business questions, break them into actionable components, and guide stakeholders toward clear, commercially sound decisions.

This role will initially carry full responsibility for the group's FP&A function and is suited to someone ready to operate at a senior level with significant autonomy and accountability. This is a highly visible role suited to someone who thrives in a fast-paced environment and takes accountability for outcomes.

You'll be expected to:

Budgets and forecasts:

Own and lead the annual budgeting process and rolling forecasts (e.g. 3+9), ensuring assumptions are commercially grounded and clearly documented

Develop robust scenario modelling and continuously refine forecasting methodologies o improve accuracy and reliability.

Commercial analysis and decision support:

Evaluate store, market, and product-level profitability, including detailed unit economics analysis

Translate financial data into practical, actionable insights for Operations, Marketing, HR, and other departments

Lead structured problem-solving initiatives on commercial questions (e.g. new store economics, pricing architecture, labour optimisation, real estate decision making), using a hypothesis-driven and data-backed approach

Proactively identify areas where performance gaps exist, diagnose root causes, and develop clear, prioritised action plans in partnership with stakeholders.

Management reporting and board support:

Deliver weekly flash P&L reporting with clear, concise commentary on trends, risks, and emerging issues

Lead monthly management and Board reporting, ensuring accuracy, clarity, and strong commercial insight

Process improvement and FP&A development:

Strengthen reporting processes, controls, and data integrity across the FP&A function

Improve the structure, usability, and impact of financial dashboards and reporting

Play a key role in shaping and scaling the finance function as the business grows.




If you want to play a part in shaping the future of real food, we'd love to hear from you! Apply today.

Who we are

Embark on an exciting opportunity with the Sorbent Paper Company, Australia's premier tissue suppliers since 1952, as we spearhead innovation and sustainability in the global paper industry. Through collaboration and resilience, we ensure the consistent delivery of Australia's favourite tissue products. With long-standing relationships with retailers built on trust, we uphold a solid foundation of customer satisfaction.

When you join us, you become part of a team across Australia and a workplace where everyone is welcome, supported and valued. We are always seeking talented people to join our team and help us grow. Are you ready to make a difference?




About the role

We’re hiring an FP&A Manager to lead Financial Planning & Analysis and business partnering across our Australia business. This is a hands‑on role that partners with Sales, Marketing, Product, Manufacturing, Supply Chain and Operations to drive planning, forecasting, costing and performance insights for an iconic FMCG brand.




Key responsibilities

Lead end‑to‑end FP&A for the business, including budgeting, forecasting and the annual planning cycle.

Act as a business partner to Sales, Marketing, Product, Manufacturing, Supply Chain and Operations to ensure strategic and commercial alignment.

Deliver consolidated financial reporting and commercial insights to provide visibility into trading performance and operational drivers.

Perform manufacturing cost accounting and margin analysis to support pricing, cost control and product profitability initiatives.

Provide business performance analysis and build commercial acumen through data‑driven recommendations that support decision‑making across functions.

Manage and mentor a small team of FP&A analysts.

Collect, interpret and review financial and operational data to inform strategy and continuous improvement.

Develop and implement strategies to minimise financial risk and improve commercial and operational outcomes.

Drive FP&A process improvements and enhancements to reporting and systems.




What we’re looking for

Tertiary degree in Accounting, Finance or related field. CA/CPA qualification is essential.

Proven FP&A experience across commercial and operational domains (Sales, Marketing, Manufacturing, Supply Chain/Operations); FMCG or manufacturing experience is highly regarded.

Demonstrated good understanding in manufacturing cost accounting, margin analysis and delivering best‑practice FP&A, reporting and systems improvements.

Experience partnering with multifunctional stakeholders with excellent communication and relationship‑management skills.

Strong analytical capability, attention to detail and the ability to see the “big picture.”

Comfortable working in a fast‑paced environment with competing priorities.

Experience with SAP and Power BI is preferred but not essential.




What we offer

Free monthly product allocations.

A pivotal role within the Finance Team with strong visibility and the opportunity to influence commercial and operational decisions.

The chance to work for an iconic household FMCG brand.




Our people, surrounding communities, and brands are at the center of our business. With an exciting future ahead of us, you can be part of a team that market and sell established and recognised products used in homes across Australia every day.

So come and join us to be part of this success story.

Before you apply, are you:

Energetic: You can tackle any situation with enthusiasm and determination.

Enthusiastic: You're highly motivated and naturally enthusiastic about what you do and that's reflected in the way you behave and talk.

Empathetic: You are friendly, personable and a team player. You genuinely care about providing exceptional service to our customers, clients, and staff members.



Secure Parking is one of the largest commercial car park operators in Australia and New Zealand, owned by Park24 Co., Ltd. Our vision is to lead our markets by delivering a seamless customer experience, guided by our core values: People First, Resilience, Integrity, Daring, and Passionate.

We are looking for a Data & AI Engineer who will play a critical role in efficacious data platforms in terms of efficiency, reliability and scalability. This role ensures implementing and maintaining advanced data and introducing AI solutions within the Microsoft Fabric ecosystem.

Key responsibilities include designing and maintaining robust data pipelines, monitoring workflow processes, integrating AI/ML components, and optimising platform and query performance, all while enforcing data management and governance standards. The Data & AI Engineer collaborates closely with application developers and commercial analysts to ensure data integrity and platform reliability, acting as the link between big data and commercial outcomes.



Major Duties:


Data Engineering and platforms- design, enhance and maintain data pipelines and data warehouse leveraging Microsoft Fabric components. Ensure data quality and documentation across the lifecycle.
Data Management - monitor data platform performance and implement infrastructure enhancements to maintain optimal benchmarks. Seamlessly support monitoring of upstream production DBs and workflows.
Data Governance - Design and enforce security policies (RBAC, RLS and PII) while owning data lineage, cataloguing and metadata management. Provide guidance and mentorship to technical and commercial analysts.
Drive FinOps- ensure costs are kept within defined budget performing cost attribution analysis and optimise the efficiency.
Automate routine tasks and operational checks using Python.
AI & Machine Learning Integration - collaborate with data scientists and cross-functional teams to deploy machine learning models to cloud environments.
Collaboration & Communication - work closely with international cross-functional teams including commercial analysts, application developers, data scientists to understand business needs and translate them into technical requirements.


Qualifications, Certifications & Licenses


Essential
Three or more years of experience in data engineering, data analytics, or related data domains.
Solid understanding of ETL/ELT and warehousing principles, and their implementation.
Strong hands-on experience across the Azure data stack, such as Azure Databricks, Data Factory, and Data Lake.
Advanced SQL and PySpark skills for transformation and validation.
Solid understanding of data management including governance and privacy policy.
Ability to work autonomously, adaptively manage competing priorities while leading and mentoring collaborators.
A bachelor's degree in computer science, Information Technology, or a related field or equivalent.
Beneficial
Hands-on experience with the Microsoft Fabric data platform.
Experience with DevOps concepts, CI/CD workflows, and source control (Azure DevOps preferred).
Creating tools and scripts to visualise and interpret large datasets.
Strong communication skills with the ability to engage respectfully with multicultural and non-technical stakeholders.
Experience in Power BI or other BI tools for visualisation and reporting support.
Proficiency in configuring and utilising cloud monitoring and logging tools to proactively detect and address operational incidents.
Solid understanding of MLOps.

About DDEG

DDEG is one of Australia’s leading performance-based engineering and building compliance consultancies, trusted for turning complex regulatory challenges into clear, achievable solutions. With more than a decade of experience and a national team of specialists, we help clients realise their design ambitions through innovative thinking across fire safety engineering, accessibility, acoustics, vibration, façade design, building solutions and sustainable design.

What defines us is our culture of curiosity, collaboration and technical excellence. We work closely across disciplines to deliver regulator-ready advice, practical strategies and confident pathways forward. Joining DDEG means contributing to safer, smarter and more sustainable buildings across Australia, while growing within a team that values creativity, shared expertise and meaningful impact.

The Role:

We are seeking a Business Systems Analyst (BSA) to translate business operations, compliance knowledge, and reporting logic into scalable digital systems. This role sits at the intersection of business, process, AI, and external vendors, owning the definition and delivery of internal systems and automation initiatives.

You will act as the primary link between stakeholders and technical vendors, ensuring business logic is clearly captured, documented, and implemented across AI solutions, automation workflows, and internal tools.

This is a senior, hands-on role with direct influence over system design, governance, and rollout across the organisation.

Key responsibilities include:

Business Analysis, Requirements & Product Ownership

Work closely with consultants, directors, and operational staff to capture business knowledge, logic, and system requirements

Translate business needs into clear functional requirements, process definitions, and system decision flows

Act as the single source of truth for system requirements across internal teams and external vendors

Contribute to the functional design of AI-powered automation tools, including facilitating SME workshops, capturing edge cases, and validating outputs

Review system and AI outputs for correctness, robustness, and alignment with business expectations, controlling scope and preventing drift

Process Optimisation, Automation & Systems Oversight

Document current-state (“as-is”) processes and design future-state (“to-be”) workflows incorporating automation, AI-assisted steps, and improved controls

Identify inefficiencies, duplication, risk points, and opportunities for automation or simplification

Maintain a holistic view of internal systems, integrations, and data ownership

Prevent fragmented tooling, duplicated solutions, and unnecessary complexity

Support scalable, maintainable system design without over-engineering

Vendor Management, Delivery & Adoption

Act as a point of contact for vendors delivering AI, automation, VBA, and system solutions

Oversee implementation, documentation, version control, and governance of automation assets

Review vendor outputs critically to ensure quality, value, and alignment to requirements

Support testing, rollout, training, and adoption of new systems to ensure they are embedded into day-to-day operations

Skills and Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Information Systems, IT, Business, Engineering, or related field

Experience in Business Analysis, Systems Analysis, or Product Ownership

Familiarity with AI, automation, or RPA tools

Knowledge of process mapping, workflow design, or process improvement methodologies

Experience managing vendors or technical implementation projects

Optional certifications that strengthen candidacy

Benefits

At DDEG, we invest in our team’s growth because our success is built together. Alongside competitive pay, we provide a supportive environment where you can belong, develop, and make a real impact. Some of the benefits include:

Ad Text:
Do you want your work to make a difference for NSW?

We are seeking a strategic and technically accomplished Manager, Energy Modelling and Analytics to lead the development and implementation of advanced energy data models and business intelligence capabilities for the NSW electricity and gas systems. This team is part of the Data & Analytics branch in Energy, Climate Change and Sustainability.

About You

You are an experienced leader with expertise in energy systems modelling, quantitative analysis and strategic policy development.

Strong background in energy market modelling (electricity and/or gas).
Advanced quantitative and analytical capability.
Experience leading multidisciplinary teams and complex projects.
Demonstrated ability to translate technical insights into clear executive advice.

Essential Requirements

The Department of Climate Change, Energy, the Environment and Water (DCCEEW) works to protect the state’s environment and heritage. It leads the way on climate change, driving the sustainable transition to a net zero economy, powered by affordable, reliable, and clean energy.

The Department’s Energy, Climate Change and Sustainability (ECCS) Group leads strategic policy, programs and major initiatives on climate change, renewable energy, energy reliability and affordability, environmental sustainability.

Ad Text:
About the business

Our client is a specialist Australian real estate private credit and investment manager with a strong and growing footprint in land development and real assets. Their property arm focuses on the acquisition, feasibility, structuring and delivery of large-scale residential and mixed-use projects across Australia.

As their development pipeline continues to expand, they are seeking a highly analytical Investment Analyst to support investment and development decisions through best-in-class financial modelling and commercial analysis.

The opportunity

You will sit at the heart of the investment and development decision-making process, building and refining complex 3-way financial models that assess project feasibilities, returns, funding structures and risk scenarios.

Your work will directly influence which projects proceed, how they are structured, and how capital is deployed. This is not a reporting or month-end role – it is a commercial, forward-looking and decision-facing position. If you enjoy working in Excel, solving complex problems and seeing your analysis translate into real-world outcomes, this will be right up your alley.

Key responsibilities
Build, maintain and enhance detailed 3-way financial models (P&L, cash flow, balance sheet)
Develop land development feasibilities and investment models
Support acquisition underwriting and project evaluation
Perform sensitivity analysis, scenario modelling and stress testing
Analyse funding structures, returns and project economics
Assist with investment papers, board materials and decision packs
Continuously improve modelling frameworks and assumptions
Provide commercial insights to senior stakeholders
About you

You may come from a background such as:

Investment analysis
Corporate finance / transaction services / advisory
Development feasibilities or property analysis
Infrastructure or project finance
Valuations or modelling teams
You will ideally have:

Advanced Excel skills (essential)
Strong experience building 3-way models from scratch
A highly analytical and logical mindset
A degree in Finance, Economics, Mathematics, Engineering or similar
Strong attention to detail
The ability to translate numbers into clear commercial insights
Why this role?
High-impact, decision-facing position
Exposure to real capital deployment and development projects
Strong learning curve and career progression
Work closely with senior investment and development leaders

CAE Overview

At CAE, we equip people in critical roles with the expertise and solutions to create a safer world. As a technology company, we digitalize the physical world, deploying software-based simulation training and critical operations support solutions. Above all else, we empower pilots, cabin crew, airlines, and defence and security forces to perform at their best every day and when the stakes are the highest. Around the globe, we’re everywhere customers need us to be with more than 13,000 employees in approximately 250 sites and training locations in over 40 countries. CAE represents more than 75 years of industry firsts—the highest-fidelity flight and mission simulators as well as training programs powered by digital technologies. We embed sustainability in everything we do. Today and tomorrow, we’ll make sure our customers are ready for the moments that matter.

Overview

This is an exciting opportunity for a Senior Financial Analyst who likes to be hands-on, drive improvement through analytics and work collaboratively with the business. In this role, you will own forecasting, budgeting, reporting, and providing insights that help drive the organisation’s growth. You will deliver insightful analysis, constructive challenges, and clear visibility into business performance, forecasting and operational drivers.

This role will be hired a full time, 6-month fixed term contract (Parental Leave Cover).

The role we are offering you

Lead the end-to-end monthly forecasting cycle, ensuring accuracy, timeliness and alignment with business expectations.

Drive the annual budgeting process, coordinating inputs across departments and ensuring alignment with strategic and financial objectives.

Own cash flow forecasting and working capital management.

Coordinate and consolidate financial data across the IPAC region, ensuring accuracy.

Our ideal candidate has:

Extensive experience in FP&A, corporate finance or business partnering

Hands-on experience with ERP and BI systems

Can showcase strong analytical and problem-solving skills

Proven experience presenting financial information to senior management and influencing business decisions

Location:

Homebush, NSW

We operate a hybrid working approach.

What CAE offers you:

Opportunity to make a positive impact on Australian defence and security

Exciting career paths in a truly global business

Access to a generous ADF Reserve Service Policy

Security requirements

As Principal Statistician/Analyst within the Statistical Collections, Evaluation and Analysis Group in QGSO you lead a team of statisticians that manages survey design, data collection, data processing, data analysis, reporting of results and statistical advice. The survey projects you lead will generally be large-scale official surveys conducted under legislative provisions on a cost-recovery basis for Queensland Government Departments. Client-funded surveys are conducted according to budgets, timelines and expectations that are agreed upon with clients under formal agreements.

THE KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

Lead project teams and manage activities to ensure outputs satisfy office standards for integrity, accuracy and timeliness based on quality principles and methodologies.
Provide technical advice and support to statisticians on statistical survey processes, analysis and reporting.
Provide statistical analysis and advice to clients and senior officers, including undertaking high level statistical analysis and providing advice on a broad range of statistical matters.
Undertake high level research, analysis and review of issues and provide recommendations.
Liaise with a range of clients including local, commonwealth and state government agencies, academic institutions, private sector organisations and the public.

SUCCESS CRITERIA

To be successful in this role you will need to:

Demonstrate experience in leading teams, projects and official client-funded surveys.
Have very good knowledge of a broad range of statistical survey methodologies.
Have experience in or an ability to work with statisticians who use the statistical software application “R” to clean, process and analyse structured and unstructured data.
